Sorry, I made a mistake while typing out my definition of pseudo atheist.  It was meant to say someone who claims to disbelieve in all manifestations of god(claims to be an atheist) while leaving out some forms of the deities from their scope.  For example, someone who claims that god cannot exist because omnipotence is impossible.  Outside of the judeo-christian family of religions, there aren't many omnipotent gods.(I haven't researched all of them, but then again, I haven't found any omnipotent gods from non-judeo-christian religions.)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Fun with numbers, you make an infinite number of things in the unuiverse and make it infinitely likely that one is a god, of course it will work out that atheism is wrong. I however would have made it infinitely UNlikely that one was a god.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
